#ramadan #muslim

Ramadan Kareem! 🌙 ✨ We asked some cool friends to share a message in light of Ramadan going digital this year. Throughout Ramadan we will be partnering with @instagram in hope to share positivity and promote kindness throughout this #MonthOfGood. Stay tuned for more posts promoting good and let’s see if you can spot some familiar faces.. 😉 
#ramadan #muslim

Be sure to thank all the people who took part in this message 💙
— 
@ayshaharun @saraahdii @neelam_ @aint.afraid @slim_slimmofication @amani @shaunking @ilham @mrmoudz @sarasabry @offendum @sisibolatini @snake @ahmedeldin @thankyouriz @allthingsfatima @drcraigconsidine @thisiskayem

Tyla Harrison-Hunt (@tylahunt) is a native Māori who converted to Islam at the Al-Noor mosque seven years ago in Christchurch, New Zealand. In this video, Tyla recounts the lost of two family members and the lost of many friends during an Islamophobic driven attack that took place at two mosques in Christchurch. Tyla also reflects on forgiveness and the aftermath of the incident that lead to the death of 51 Muslims. // Video edited by @shaymaalshiri + @snake // tags: #christchurch #christchurchshooting #christchurchmosqueshooting #muslim #islam #quran #newzealand

BREAKING 🚨 European Union court rules hijab can be banned at work.

Source - @aljazeeraenglish 

#muslim #muslimnews #islam

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Muslim on July 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text.

Photo shared by Muslim on July 15, 2021 tagging @aljazeeraenglish. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎الجزيرة ALJAZEERA LIVE News Religion Top EU court rules hijab can be banned at work European Union court rules companies may ban Muslim employees from wearing a headscarf under certain conditions.‎'‎.

Photo by Muslim on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The European Union' top court has ruled that employers may forbid the wearing of visible symbols of religious or political belief, such as headscarves.'.

Photo by Muslim on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"A prohibition on wearing any visible form of expression of political, philosophical or religious beliefs in the workplace may be justified by the employer's need to present a neutral image towards customers or to prevent social disputes," the court said.'.

Photo by Muslim on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"However, that justification must correspond to a genuine need on the part of the employer and, in reconciling the rights and interests at issue, the national courts may take into account the speific context of their Member State and, in particular, more favourable national provisions on the protection of freedom of religion."'.

Photo by Muslim on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Suspended from work The case was brought to court by two women in Germany who were suspended from their jobs after they started wearing hijab, a headscarf worn by many Muslim women who feel it is part of their religion.'.

Photo by Muslim on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'They were told by their respective employer that this was not allowed, and were at different points either suspended, told to come to work without it or put on a different job, court documents show.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Muslim on July 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says '@muslim Source Gamespot Indonesian Minister calls for Fortnite to be banned in Indonesia over a user generated map resembling the Kaaba 10'.

Photo shared by Muslim on July 12, 2021 tagging @gamespot. May be an image of text that says 'An Indonesian Minister has called for Fortnite to be banned in the country due to user-generated map that allows for an in-game creation of a holy structure to be destroyed. As reported by CNN Indonesia and GamesIndustry.biz Minister for Indonesian Tourism and Creative Economy Sandiaga Uno has announced plans to ban Fortnite in the country after the discovery of a user-created map that allegedly allows for players to destroy a building resembling the Kaaba, a sacred site for Muslims.'.
Photo by Muslim on July 12, 2021. May be an image of text.

Photo by Muslim on July 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"The game Fortnite is directly against lofty values, especially religious ones,' Sandiaga said in a statement. "This can trigger disrespectful behavior between religious communities and encourage acts of violence." Sandiaga said that he instructed a team to investigate the situation and issue ban, hoping this would "warn some game developers to be careful."'.

Photo by Muslim on July 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Fortnite F June 36 PM Fortnite woulo like to clarify something about desecration of places of worship in the game The content referred to was an island made by a player creative mode Creative where on the island you can't destroy the Holy Kaaba. We would like to emphasize that our team respects all religions and works closely with our game content makers to provide a safe gaming experience for all our players.
